76	/// Map a [`ProcNr`] to its index in the process table.
77	///
78	/// Kernel tasks (negative `nr`) land in slots `[0, NR_TASKS)`; user processes
79	/// land in `[NR_TASKS, N_PROC_SLOTS)`. Returns `None` if `nr` is outside the
80	/// allocated range.
